 :tx/rationale "Create task: SPEC-SELF-COHERENCE: Formalize INV-QUERY-026 (Index Obligation) + ADR on self-coherence as a fitness dimension. BACKGROUND: After PERF-2 wires all indexes, formalize the principle so the bilateral loop enforces it going forward. Two spec additions: (1) INV-QUERY-026: Index Obligation — 'Every read path that selects datoms by a known attribute MUST use store.attribute_datoms() (AEVT index) rather than store.datoms() with runtime filtering. Similarly for entity_datoms() (EAVT) and vaet_referencing() (VAET). Falsification: any code path where store.datoms() is followed by an attribute/entity equality check with a compile-time-known target.' (2) ADR-COHERENCE-NNN: Self-Coherence Dimension — 'Correctness is necessary but not sufficient. An implementation must use its own declared capabilities wherever they apply. The Capability Utilization Ratio CUR(C) = paths_using(C) / paths_that_should_use(C) measures internal coherence. Utilization becomes the eighth F(S) component alongside coverage, depth, coherence, completeness, formality, certainty, commitment.' This ADR elevates the 'Implemented But Not Wired' failure mode from a pattern observation to a formal specification concern. The trace scanner can be extended to check index utilization (detect store.datoms() + attribute filter anti-pattern) as part of the bilateral forward scan. APPROACH: (1) braid spec create INV-QUERY-026 with statement, falsification, verification. (2) braid spec create ADR-COHERENCE-001 with problem, options, decision, consequences. (3) Optionally: extend trace scanner to detect the anti-pattern and report as a gap. ACCEPTANCE: (A) INV-QUERY-026 exists in store and spec/03-query.md. (B) ADR-COHERENCE-001 exists in store and spec/20-coherence.md. (C) bilateral.rs and trilateral.rs have 0 violations (verified by PERF-2). DEPENDS-ON: PERF-2 (t-7ff62b3a). FILE: spec/03-query.md + spec/20-coherence.md. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-001, ADR-STORE-005."
